author: Renea Blackheart
text:
Perhaps things will never be the same.
Perhaps my life will never truly be "normal."
But is that really a bad thing?
If I had the chance to reverse time and stop all of this from happening... It's strange to say this, but I wouldn't take it. 
So much has happened to me, good and bad.
I have to keep moving forward. I have to go on. I have to protect those I care about. Normality, things coming to a close, this era of my life coming to an end scares me. In an attempt to fill the void left by a lack of social interaction, I habe found self esteem and purpose... What will happen when that void is filled once again by what left it there in the first place?
There's really only one way to find out.
There's no way to stop it, so I have to face it head on. I'll worry about it when I get there. But for now...
I'll just continue my experience until it is no more.

author: Sigmarth Cipherius
text:
Internet Checkpoint Journal Entry 2 
I've seen gameplays of Primal Dialga after first hearing the theme (and before discovering taia777's checkpoint). It's very commanding yet soothing at the same time, it screams "you've reached this far dear traveler, now show me what you've learn in your journey, from the scars you bear, the fights you encounter, the tears you shed, to the friends you made, the lessons you learnt, and the sacrifices you made to get here." Dialga itself is the beast of time, and to see it harness the power of Primal way before ORAS gave me chills. 

2021, a year that we should keep our guards up as history taught us. The passing of that year became months, weeks, days, hours and minutes. By the time we look back on it, it's an archival of what we faced and broke through. What we've celebrated and what we've fight for may be a footprint in history, but that's what makes our stories on this world. 

I'm currently taking my next semester, which means I won't be getting on the drawing block more often. To the kind people who commented on my last entry, thank you for the kind words from the bottom of your heart, I'll take some spare time off to improve on my drawings. Speaking of drawing, I might need to draw Hope more often.

The year of the Ox, 2021, the cold winter isn't over yet. I wish we'll meet again in spring.

I've had my dreams come true and be crushed, my frozen heart thawed and I learned to truly love again, I've met some amazing people who I've helped and who've helped me through some tough times. I've worked in three different industries, and am still somehow unemployed. I've built a budding community of my own, with the help of an amazing group of people I can truly call my best friends, despite only knowing a few of them in person.  My whole perspective on life and its meaning has been flipped on its head a half dozen times. I've flipped from being depressed, to excited about life, and back. I've gone from somewhat jaded to infatuated to finally realizing my old traumas and what it did to me. Its a confusing time for everyone, but I want anyone reading this to know know that you'll get through this.

As this year of strife ends, all we can do is look forward to the future. Try and see the good in what's happened. Take all the positive changes and run with it. Don't let the negativity set your perspective on life because there's to much more.

author: Quinn Daniels

Checkpoint:

As I write this, I'm putting off homework and sitting in my room at my Dad's house at 3:47AM. I visited home for the first time in weeks, and I will be travelling back to my college campus tomorrow night.

Last night — well, Sunday night — I completely messed up how I handled an argument with my mom. I expressed that I want to seek Hormone Replacement Therapy to begin medically transitioning. I've went through transitioning socially for months now, and on my college campus, I'm happier than I've ever been, despite my constant financial struggles and overwhelmingly large work load as a digital media student. I have friends and an extended family member that supports me, and it doesn't feel like I have to hide such an integral part of my identity anymore.

I came out to my parents long before I publicly came out on social media. At times though, it feels like they make no effort to acknowledge me for who I am, rather than who they thought I was.

On Sunday night, my mother made it starkly clear to me that she wouldn't even try to understand or sympathize. She also made it clear that our insurance doesn't cover HRT, and that she wouldn't help in paying for it either.

Tonight, I talked with my Dad about what happened Sunday night, and while he still misgendered and deadnamed me (I didn't correct him, though...), he did this best to listen to me and not just overpower the conversation and belittle me like my mother does. It... It hurt at first. When the subject came up, he impulsively asked why I was "setting myself up for heartbreak". But... After talking more about it with him, and even showing him the picture I posted on National Coming Out Day, I know that he meant well in the end. I like to believe the same for my mother, but with behavior that she has shown in the past, it's unlikely.

While I don't know why I feel compelled to write here, I hadn't really had a chance to vent about a lot of that. I feel better though, so I guess I needed it.

Anyway, thank you for reading all of this. We can all be main characters.

author: AnywhereAndNowhere
text:
Checkpoint: I talked with my mom today about my concerns about my inability to access my childhood memories. We had a really in-depth talk about the different events that could be linked to it, the different traumas I've had to endure in my early life, and she asked me what I hoped to achieve in my life 3-5 years in the future. I'm turning 20 this month, in exactly 9 days, and I've never cried harder over having to admit to my mother that what I wanted out of my life felt too far out of my own reach. 

She suggested I give therapy a second chance (I went before in my preteens for severe depression, but stopped going because my therapist at the time told me I was wasting her time), and I'm considering it. I feel like whatever it is I've suppressed from my childhood is what has been holding me back from becoming the mature adult I know I could and should be. I want to know, more than anything, because it feels like I'm missing something- like something is wrong with me, but I can't comprehend what it is yet. 

On a separate note, I've come to terms with the fact that I fell in love with a girl who I had agreed to be no strings attached with, a girl who is both my best friend and a person I feel most in-tune with intimately. Yet I know that she cannot return my feelings, because she has her own trauma she's working through in her own way. I want to be there for her, and I want to show her that I'm there for her no matter how far down the rabbit hole she goes. I want to be her rock, despite neither of us having much stability in our lives. 

I know it might take years, but I don't see myself giving up on her, and I know she feels strongly enough to want to stay with me in the long run too. She's slowly coming out of her shell with me, and slowly becoming more open to the possibility of us. 

Improvement and commitment are both really difficult, but we're learning and taking it day by day, and for that I'm willing to keep pushing onwards, no matter how many times I fall into despair or succumb to melancholy. 

For you, Hanna, I feel like I can get by each day and not feel like my world is falling apart at the seams. 
I know you'll only find this when the universe decides it's time for you to, so I'll say it here. 
I love you so very much, with every fibre of your being. Your flaws and imperfections are what make you the gentle and caring person you are, and I love you as you are. 
I hope that when you find this, you come to realize that love and romance still exist and are worth believing in. That you are worth believing in those things, and you are the reason why I can say these things with confidence. 
I hope you can believe in love, like I believe in you. 

10/3/2020

author: Mattia cicchetti
text:
I'll never forget that moment. That moment when the first time I cried. Cried for something that heartless being would dare to say "meaningless". A moment which I couldn't and won't never forget. Started the game in the worst day of my life, a day which in I would have been existed anymore, seeing a lifeless pokemon with no friends, no ideas, no will to live... But, like a spark of the true essence of light, there it is, he fights for what he truly believes, for what should be always seen, he never gives up, he never tries to flee like a coward... NO! He stands up everytime and everytime and doesn't matter if he loses several *times*... No... He knows he can do it, he must do it, for the sake of the world, for what they truly must believe in. And even at challenges of true hell, he never spaces out, he fights forward, to fight the darkness inside of the world, inside of himself. Thinking about descovering the true meanings of Emotion, Wisdom and Will, fighting for make disappear the fears of who need, let know that everyone can be what truly wants to be: A friend, a good friend, a teacher, a guy that yells at you just to make sure that you don't make stupid things, a good spirit that tries to calm the needing souls of everybody, a crazy guy who just want to be noticed for once, a girl that just to want everyone having fun and of course also herself, a clumsy guy that want to be happy for and either with his friends, rageful persons who show a good heart tough, guys that have fun in their journeys, and most of all... A true leader who really knows what being a leader truly is. destroying all the evil heartless beings who locked in his gate... But now he understand that being strong isn't enough, thinking that it's all over, the Truth fills him and all his hopes. It's time, you can do it, you must do it, destroying the dark power, fighting for you truly believe in. The time is right, that your dreams, your hopes and whishes be the reality. And after a long trip, you climb all of your insicurities and you are straight to the one must be freed. Someone that suffered more than everyone else. Fighting for you truly believe always been the mantra of your life, even at those times when you couldn't do anything. Go! Never let up! Even if you will disappear, no one will forget you, no one will regret to have been with you, everybody understood who you are, a friend and most of all, the savior of a world near the the end of everything. You did it, you saved the life of the ruler of time, but it doesn't end now, no, he has understood thathe was pathetic to let darkness control his being, but you did it. To thank you he gives you the most noble and important gift: Life. All of your friends come to you, crying for seeing you again, cheering you and everyone else up that you saved the world and even the God of time himself is proud of you, you are the value of values: Hope. You are hope, you are everything. Thank you.
.... I will never forget these moments, I have been grown with these moments. And now I want to say something to you, to those who have read my entire comment, when you are sad, angry, or scared, remember of you can do it, remember that none can destroy your will to live and your own Time and Space. That's what it truly is: Fighting to the end. Always think you can save the world and the universe from the bottom of death. At least, fellas ,this is what this true game teached to me. Have always a good and joyful day and never forget that you can do everything.



Even believing on your own Time and Space

text:
I would say...it’s a small channel with extended versions of music, combined with a checkpoint system that ended spanning the entire channel, and the recommendation system recommending this channel’s videos to the most random of people.
Those random people share their experiences through checkpoints, even those that are normally silent.
The checkpoint system is what makes this channel unique, combined with the dead status of the channel and how not-fancy it is, like Taia’s own private checkpoint, in the music that happened to speak to them.
Though, that’s quite far-fetched, I do admit. Probably just save extended tracks that they really liked, before being either forgotten or expired, with a few people starting a trend here of a checkpoint system, relying on the recommendations to bring you back again, like a really weird public diary. 
A world built from nothing, based in life and games and YouTube.

I have no idea if that answers your question or not, but it’s at least food for thought.
As for a more mainstream approach; a unique community and nostalgic music.

author: mc cheshire
text:
Checkpoint: 
Just got two cats. This is the second worst my depression has ever gotten, but there is a certain icy calm to it all. I feel like a giant robot, unable to feel true emotion, but nonetheless amused by the tiny fluffs antics. They've woken me up at 6am every day this week, but I don't complain. Usually I do my best to spend as much time as possible unconscious, but the mornings bring a solitude I can endure, and one I am unfamiliar with. They sleep on my bed with me; these days I keep having nightmares of my past, with every horrible moment stitched together in a worst hits compilation. I see Maggie getting hit by that truck and bleeding out in the street. I see the man who jumped off his roof across the street, splattered on the cement like a chunky paintball. I see me in first grade, not knowing that teachers shouldn't touch students like that. I feel my broken jaw again, I feel the pains in my leg when I'm awake again. This is my first checkpoint I've written down. It's comforting, putting myself out there, somewhere. I almost get to feel like I'm reading my own words as somebody else. I wish I loved myself; I wish I felt like I deserved it. I wish had someone who would show me I am. I wish none of it ever happened. I wish my mom didn't steal my cereal. Sometimes the little things are the punctuation to a big sentence, and it's enough to break the surface tension and flood the dam. 
I think I'm choosing a new name; I've had too many people call me my old one while they hurt me, and now all I can think of is the pains. I don't know how to accept that I'm evolving, and I'm afraid the few people I care about won't accept me. I miss feeling loved. I haven't been hugged since March 16, 2017. I feel as if I have lost my humanity.
-River, signing off. May 21, 2020. 
You are the main character.
